    "created_at": "2016-05-11T00:07:38Z",
    "updated_at": "2016-05-11T00:07:38Z",
    "body": "What about this... show the `OK` button, don't show the `X`? That seems more user friendly to me: `OK` is focused by default (and thus can be dismissed with spacebar), `OK` means \"I accept this information\" instead of \"Get this information out of here\", and it's a bigger click target for mouse users. Seems like you can do it by following [this StackOverflow answer](http://stackoverflow.com/a/13191205).\n"
  },
